</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uelmasoulseer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ElmaSoulseer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#333333>(6/9/02 6:28:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1327.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Verant's response to seriously overpowered NPCs</span><hr size=1> Something you are missing Screwed is Melee Upgrades verses Caster Upgrads.<br>
<br>
Take your best level 60 melee equiped with Luclin loot (non Vex thal or keyed akheva level) and velious gear, and take him to solb.<br>
<br>
What happens?<br>
<br>
Now, take your best level 60 caster, with the best luclin loot and velious gear.<br>
<br>
What happens?<br>
<br>
The melee will tear through solb solo. I am sure that they could deal with the efreeti solo, or damn near close.<br>
<br>
That caster? Well, if its not a wizard, that caster will perform almost exactly the same as they did when kunark was out.<br>
<br>
Every expansion, Melee's AC, HP and Damage output jump by leaps and bounds, but the casters AC, HP and Damage output, jump, heh they don't &quot;jump&quot; they go up slightly (with wizards being the exception, but even they are not near melee jump).<br>
<br>
