<br>
Yet, with every expansion, THAT IS EXACTLY what melee's are capable of doing.<br>
<br>
<br>
This is called &quot;Mudflation&quot; where the influx of new gear causes old content to become less difficult, or even eventually trivial.<br>
<br>
The &quot;New Content&quot; mobs did not need this &quot;boost&quot; to make them of the appropriate difficulty. The trash mobs already quad for 250-450, flurry, and cast 1k nukes.<br>
<br>
Now, they quad for 250-450, and cast 2.2k Ancient Nukes that drop only off of the Emperor himself.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile level 35's trying to do FULL GROUPS in Nurga are getting nuked for 300-500 a pop from all the casters.<br>
<br>
Are you telling me that a level 35 player can deal with 2-3 mobs chain casting for 300-500? When at level 35 they have 600-1400 hp tops.<br>
<br>
Level 30, green to 56 wurms in GD casting level 56 nukes for 1k? Killing the level 40's hunting them for quest pieces in one shot instantly?<br>
<br>
Level 60's fighting level 44-47 frogs in Seblis, getting hit by Ice comet for full damage, every time, with over 160 CR, while said mob double hits for 145?<br>
