Last time I checked, the  release of Velious and Luclin didn't change the low end game, other than to add new content.  If anything, it made good equipment EASIER to obtain... look at items like Lammies- Once an uber sword, now a 2K item.  Knuckle duster n jade maces have tumbled in price (hell, anyone using KDs any more?).  I remember SolB FG raids, and people getting awesome gear like Mithril.... and a certain level 45+ ranger in KEG who wore Silver Plated Leggings for ages, even after hitting Fear and getting a few pieces of Thorny Vine (hi Wick).  Anyone actually using Fear/Hate gear?  Most have better by the time they're planable anyways.  Caster gear has followed a parallel course.  Flowing black robes, Oracle robes, green silken drapes, and the once Top-Of-The-Line SMR, well, virtuallyno one wears em any more.  Druids in Brown Chitin Protectors? Hell, that's a give-it-away-to-a-newb item now, it used to make you famous.  +Int/Wis jewellery is laughable to get now.. how many casters in their 30s-40's dont have their INT capped now?<br>
